<html>
    <head>
        <title>Next Minecraft Update When?!?!?</title>
        <link href="//fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Balsamiq+Sans:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
        <style>
            html, body {
                margin: 0;
                padding: 0;
            }

            body {
                display: flex;
                justify-content: center;
                align-items: center;
                text-align: center;
                height: 100vh;
                width: 100vw;
                background-color: #220c4f;
                color: #eee;
                font-family: 'Balsamiq Sans';
                font-weight: 400;
            }

            body .please-im-begging-you {
                font-weight: 700;
                text-decoration: underline;
            }

            body a {
                color: #eee;
                text-decoration: none;
            }

            body a:hover, body a:active, body a:focus {
                color: #ccc;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div>
            <h1>Mojang releases a new Minecraft version every {{avgDays}} days on average with a standard deviation of {{stdDev}} days.</h1>
            <h1>Since the last release was {{lastReleaseDaysAgo}} days ago, the next release will probably be within the next {%if avgDiff > 0%}{{avgDiff}} to{%endif%} {{diffSum}} days.</h1>
            <h4>Or, you know, maybe not. It'll be ready when it's ready. You don't like bugs, do you?</h4>
            <h4>Seriously, this is just looking at historical dates. <span class="please-im-begging-you">We can't predict the future, so please don't ask us to.</span></h4>
            <p><small>Made by <a href="https://github.com/simpleauthority" target="_blank">simple</a></small></p>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>